## 3. Component Guide

### 3.1 [main.py](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py) — FastAPI Application
| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [lifespan()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#31-65) | Startup: connects MCP client, builds agent graph. Shutdown: disconnects. |
| [get_current_user()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#82-88) | Validates `X-Auth-Token` header via [SecurityService](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/security.py#42-97). |
| [check_rate_limit()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#90-96) | Enforces 60 req/min per user via [RateLimiter](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/security.py#99-126). |
| [chat_endpoint()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#129-170) | Main endpoint. Sanitizes input, builds state, invokes graph. |
| [stream_chat_endpoint()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#172-220) | SSE streaming variant of chat. |
| [resume_action()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#222-251) | Human-in-the-loop: resumes a paused graph. |
| [mcp_status()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#253-266) | Lists all discovered MCP tools. |
| [_extract_logs()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#275-323) | Converts message history into structured [LogEntry](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/main.py#111-117) objects. |

### 3.2 [app/graphs/supervisor.py](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/supervisor.py) — LangGraph Agent
| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [build_agent_graph()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/supervisor.py#87-218) | Async. Fetches MCP tools, binds them to Gemini, builds the 3-node StateGraph. |
| [supervisor_node()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/supervisor.py#110-128) | The "brain". Decides tool calls, tracks `_iteration` count. |
| [validator_node()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/supervisor.py#131-167) | The "quality control". Checks if the gathered data fully answers the original query. |
| [should_act()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/supervisor.py#170-179) | Router. Tools vs. Validator. |
| [should_loop()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/supervisor.py#182-191) | Router. Repeat supervisor vs. END. |
| [_fallback_node()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/supervisor.py#225-233) | Used when MCP is unavailable. LLM without tools. |

### 3.3 [app/graphs/state.py](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/graphs/state.py) — AgentState
| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `messages` | Chat history (accumulated). |
| `access_token` | User's API token forwarded to n8n webhooks. |
| `_iteration` | Loop counter (max 10) to prevent infinite loops. |
| `_validation` | Stores the validator's verdict ("COMPLETE" / "INCOMPLETE"). |

### 3.3 [app/mcp_client.py](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/mcp_client.py) — Multi-Server MCP Client
| Method | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [connect()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/mcp_client.py#48-69) | Iterates all 3 servers, calls [get_tools()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/mcp_client.py#75-82) on each, builds `_tool_route_map`. |
| [get_tools()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/mcp_client.py#75-82) | Returns cached flat list of all tools from all servers. |
| [call_tool(name, args)](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/mcp_client.py#83-105) | Looks up server in `_tool_route_map`, opens SSE session, calls the tool. |
| [read_resource(uri)](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/mcp_client.py#106-118) | Reads a resource from a specific server. |

### 3.4 [app/security.py](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/app/security.py) — Security Layer
| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `MOCK_USERS` | Hardcoded user database (replace with OAuth2/JWT in production). |
| `SecurityService.verify_token()` | Looks up token in MOCK_USERS, returns user profile. |
| `SecurityService.sanitize_input()` | Strips prompt injection patterns, truncates long inputs. |
| `RateLimiter.is_allowed()` | Sliding-window rate limiter (60 req/min per user). |

### 3.5 [mcp_server/shared/llm_helper.py](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/mcp_server/shared/llm_helper.py) — Shared LLM
| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| [get_llm()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/mcp_server/shared/llm_helper.py#25-40) | Returns a configured `ChatVertexAI` Gemini instance. |
| [generate_answer()](file:///d:/AI_Orchestration/mcp_server/shared/llm_helper.py#53-82) | Takes raw data + system prompt → returns polished text via Gemini. |

